# Engineering Constitution Rules
# Full document: https://github.com/tlacahuepec/Constitution/blob/main/CONSTITUTION.md

# Immutable Rules
- TDD is mandatory — write failing tests BEFORE production code
- Never push directly to main or dev
- All changes go through PRs with CI passing
- No secrets ever in the repository
- No force-pushes on protected branches
- One logical change per PR (one issue per branch)
- CI must pass before any merge

# TDD Protocol (mandatory)
- Write a failing test that defines the expected behavior
- Run the test and confirm it fails
- Write the minimum code to make the test pass
- Run the test and confirm it passes
- Refactor if needed, ensuring tests still pass

# Workflow
- Branch from dev using feat/, fix/, hotfix/, or release/ prefix
- Commit messages: imperative mood, reference issue, < 72 chars
- Before pushing: run linter, formatter, and full test suite
- PR must include: issue link, summary, test plan, checklist

# Prohibited
- Never commit directly to main or dev
- Never bypass CI or skip hooks
- Never suppress lint, PMD, or static analysis warnings — fix the issue
- Never self-approve PRs
- Never commit secrets or .env files
- Never make destructive changes without human authorization
- Never skip writing tests

# Always
- Read CONSTITUTION.md before starting significant work
- Add tests for all new code
- Use SOLID principles
- Prefer small focused changes
- Follow existing patterns in the repository
